data.title: 1,060 Best Boy Names to Name Your Son in 2023
data.meta_description: This list has something for everyone, whether you're looking for a trendy or classic baby boy name. Plus pop culture baby names including some from Yellowstone.
data.text:
There's so much to consider when having a baby, but one of the most important decisions is what to name your son or daughter. For most, a name will stick with a child for his entire lifetime, so it's understandable to feel the pressure. Plus, new parents might be fielding opinions from friends and family members that can add to the stress.

In the past 10 years, there has been little movement in the top 5 baby boy names: Liam, Noah, Oliver, James, Elijah, William, Mason, Logan, Jacob, and Ethan have rotated in and out of the top of the list. Liam and Noah have claimed the top 2 spots since 2014. If you're looking for inspiration beyond the most popular baby names, check out our list below with every thing from country music-inspired names, traditional baby boy names, and other pop culture ideas.

Yellowstone-Inspired Baby Boy Names

Yellowstone was the most-watched show last year, so it stands to reason that names from the series are growing in popularity. According to the Social Security Administration, the top two names with the biggest increase in popularity from 2021 to 2022 are Dutton and Kayce. Dutton hopped nearly 1,000 spots from 1,821 to 835, and Kayce jumped from 1,077 to 587. Why not keep the trend going with more names from the show. (Just stay away from Jamie.)
